olive oil
1 potato
1 tsp honey
1 bag slaw mix
1 drizzle white wine vinegar
1 packet mayonnaise
1 parsnip
1 packet Chicken Drumstick Fillet
1 sachet Aussie Spice Blend

• Preheat oven to 240°C/220°C fan-forced.
• Cut potato and parsnip into fries.
• Place veggie fries on a lined oven tray. Season with salt, drizzle with
olive oil and toss to coat. Spread out evenly, then bake until tender,
20-25 minutes.

• When the fries have 15 minutes remaining, combine boneless chicken
drumsticks, Aussie spice blend and a drizzle of olive oil in a medium bowl.
• In a medium frying pan, heat a drizzle of olive oil over medium-high heat.
Cook chicken until browned, 2 minutes each side.
• Transfer to a second lined oven tray, drizzle over the honey and roast until
cooked through, 10-12 minutes.

TIP: Chicken is cooked through when it is no longer pink inside.

• In a second medium bowl, combine slaw mix, a drizzle of white wine
vinegar and olive oil. Season to taste.

• Slice spiced chicken.
• Divide chicken, veggie fries and slaw between plates.
• Serve with mayonnaise. Enjoy!